_json.gridTitle: One Minute Reflection – 15 February – ‘Be very attentive to what you see and believe what you do not see.’  – Mark 8:11-13
_json.description: Our Lord worked miracles and yet many despised him… They said to themselves : ‘The works are divine but, as for Him, he is only a man.’ Therefore, you see two things: divine works on the one hand and a Man on the other. If those divine works can only be carried out by God, could it not be because God is hidden in this Man? Yes. Be very attentive to what you see and believe what you do not see.
